
This directory contains experimental code, aimed toward
development of a Qt-based version of the KernelShark GUI.

Third Party Software:
------------------------------------------------------------
The external dependencies are listed below:
1. Cmake, Qt5Base, OpenGL/Glut, Python2.7, NumPy and GTest

  1.1 In order to install the packages on Ubuntu do the following:
    sudo apt-get install build-essential git cmake libjson-c-dev -y
    sudo apt-get install qtbase5-dev gksu -y
    sudo apt-get install freeglut3-dev libxmu-dev libxi-dev -y
    sudo apt-get install libpython2.7-dev cython python-numpy -y

  1.2 In order to be able to run the tests on Ubuntu do the following:
    sudo apt-get libgtest-dev -y
    cd /usr/src/gtest
    sudo cmake .
    sudo make
    sudo cp *.a /usr/lib

  2 In order to install the packages on Fedora, as root do the following:
    dnf install gcc gcc-c++ git cmake json-c-devel -y
    dnf install redhat-lsb-core beesu -y
    dnf install qt5-qtbase-devel freeglut-devel redhat-rpm-config -y
    dnf install python2-devel python2-Cython python-numpy gtest-devel -y


Building:
------------------------------------------------------------
1. Follow the instructions given in trace-cmd/README and build
the original libraries.

2. Do:
    cd ks_qtdev/build
    cmake ../
    make
